<strong>Summary</strong></p>
<p>
At Orbotix we blend robotics and augmented reality pushing the capabilities of modern mobile hardware (<a href="http://vimeo.com/53561976">http://vimeo.com/53561976</a>). We are looking for someone that is motivated, and willing to think outside the sphere! If you have interest in working with a team to bring games to market, have a great personality, and a Can-Do attitude &ndash; We would love to hear from you!</p>
<p>
<strong>Role &amp; Responsibilities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Assist&nbsp;&nbsp;a small team to create games and gaming interfaces that utilize the Sphero API.</li>
<li>
Brainstorm new augmented reality gameplay elements and concepts.</li>
<li>
Create cutting edge augmented reality gaming experiences.</li>
<li>
You will work closely with both the others on the software development team as well as the hardware engineers during implementation.</li>
<li>
Assist in&nbsp;implementing new game mechanics&nbsp;that bridges the reality of Sphero with the virtual connected environment of the smartphone in a complementary way.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<br />
<strong>Requirements</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Excellent work ethic and attention to detail.</li>
<li>
Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Computer Science, Electrical Engineering,&nbsp;or equivalent skill set.</li>
<li>
Experience with Unity 3D or similar game engine.</li>
<li>
Strong 3D Linear Algebra skills</li>
<li>
Interest in hardware and robotics.</li>
<li>
Knowledge of best practices in software design, and development.</li>
<li>
Excellent written and verbal communication skills.</li>
<li>
4+ years experience&nbsp;with C/C++</li>
<li>
Familiarity&nbsp;with&nbsp;ObjC/C#</li>
<li>
Experience with low level programming and memory management.</li>
</ul>
<p>
