<strong>Summary</strong></p>
<p>
At Orbotix we blend robotics and augmented reality pushing the capabilities of modern mobile hardware (<a href="http://vimeo.com/53561976" target="_parent">http://vimeo.com/53561976</a>).&nbsp; We are looking for a dynamic, motivated computer vision engineer to join our team in Boulder, CO.&nbsp; Responsibilities include designing cutting edge vision algorithms, interfacing new technology with our existing AR engine, solving diverse software/hardware problems, and building category-defying mobile games.</p>
<p>
If you want to share your knowledge while learning from others, work smart, and contribute to some awesome projects, we think you&rsquo;ll have a blast with us. As a bonus you&rsquo;ll get to play with robots, games and mobile devices all day long. We are willing to relocate the right person to Colorado.</p>
<p>
<br />
<strong>Requirements</strong></p>
<p>
Must have low level knowledge of modern computer vision techniques including:</p>
<ul>
<li>
SLAM technologies</li>
<li>
Pose estimation/bundle adjustment</li>
<li>
Real-time reconstruction</li>
<li>
Dense methods.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<br />
Proficiency in C/C++.<br />
Eagerness to problem solve outside your discipline.<br />
Interest in iOS and Android Development.<br />
Interest in robotics.<br />
Cooperative, independent thinker who takes personal ownership of projects.</p>
<p>
Although you are encouraged to send a traditional resume, a resume alone won&rsquo;t make you stand out. So along with your resume please send an explanation of who you are and why you would be a good fit for Orbotix. Include pictures, videos, or screenshots of your previous projects, both professional and personal. We&rsquo;re just geeks like you so don&rsquo;t hold back.</p>
<br />
<p>
<strong>About Orbotix</strong></p>
<p>
Orbotix is a venture backed startup with the vision that you shouldn&rsquo;t be limited to emailing, getting directions, and playing a game of scrabble on your mobile device. You should be able to just as easily download an app to control all of the physical devices around you. No more remotes. No more clunky interfaces. No more keys. Everything is done with the powerful mobile device that you already carry with you. We&rsquo;re looking for someone great to join our small but hardcore engineering team to help design and implement our products, starting with Sphero, a powerful robotic entertainment device.</p>
